  "text": "Growth experiments were performed in anaerobic culture tubes (166150 mm) that contained 10 ml high-salt minimal medium with the indicated substrate and a head space of N 2 /CO 2 (80 : 20) unless indicated otherwise. Tubes were sealed with a butyl rubber stopper that was secured with an aluminium crimp collar. Growth was monitored spectrophotometrically at 600 nm with a Bausch and Lomb Spectronic 20. Headspace gases were quantified by GC as described by [CITATION_1] .",
